//- this run's HAR is in the locals (browsertime.har on the summary
//- page, browsertime.run.har on run pages — the same gating the
//- waterfall cross-link uses) the rows come from the median/current
//- run's entries: one self-consistent set of timings, with start
//- offsets so requests can be drawn on the paint clock. Without a HAR
//- (Safari, old result data) the rows fall back to the pagexray shape,
